cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.OS

This paper deals with security issues related to IP headers and network protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves reverse-engineering and analysis of code, which could be classified under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper discusses the identification of devices through network protocols, which could be categorized under computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves breaking KASLR, which is a security mechanism in operating systems, and thus could be classified under systems and control (cs.SY) and operating systems (cs.OS).
